# Application Services

Hub: @src/application/use-cases/run-agent.usecase.ts orchestrates the full run loop.

## Planning vs execution

| Service | Role |
|---------|------|
| `ScenarioPlannerService` | Scenario list from demand |
| `ExecutionPlanPlannerService` | ExecutionPlan (Hybrid Guarded) |
| `ExecutionPlanFactoryService` | Safe factory fallback when LLM plan fails |
| `PlanExecutorService` | Executes plan steps |
| `PlanReplannerService` / `PlanPatchApplierService` | Replan and patch |

## Runtime support

| Service | Role |
|---------|------|
| `ActionPolicyService` | Destructive/sensitive action policy |
| `DataHarnessService` | Resolve dynamic placeholders |
| `LocatorResolverService` / `ElementAvailabilityResolverService` | Locators and availability |
| `ValidationBinderService` | Bind validations to resolved data |
| `RecoveryPolicyService` | Fallback and emergency actions |
| `BugClassifierService` | Severity from signals |
| `EvidenceService` | Run artifacts and bug folders |
| `SanitizerService` | Strip secrets before persist |
| `TaskMemoryService` | **Ephemeral** per-task state during run only |

## Rules

- Services depend on **ports**, never concrete infra adapters.
- Register new services in `APPLICATION_PROVIDERS` (@src/application/application.module.ts).
- Business logic stays here — not in `interfaces/cli/` or `infra/`.
